==English==

===Etymology===
From Afrikaans/Dutch words [[aarde]] '[[earth]]' and [[vark]] 'pig': earth-pig. Early European colonists in South-Africa perceived that animal as similar to pig. The word was loaned into English in the late 18th century.
===Noun===
Plural: aardvarks
#''(Zoölogy):'' A  [[mammal]] of the order [[Tubulidentata]], of the genus ''[[Orycteropus]]''. Its only surviving species ''[[Orycteropus afer]]'', commonly called 'aardvark', somewhat resembling a [[pig]], is common in some parts of Southern Africa. It [[burrows]] in the ground, and feeds entirely on [[ant]]s, which it [[catches]] with its long, [[slimy]] tongue.

====Synonyms====
[[African Ant Eater]] (''scientific''), [[earth pig]] (''common name''), [[ant bear]] (''alternative common name; also for the [[giant anteater]]''), [[anteater]] (''a more general common name for different species including aardvark''), [[pangolin]] (?)

